At about 15:49 on Friday afternoon Netcare911 paramedics responded to a collision on the R40 in Hazyview, Mpumalanga.When paramedics arrived at scene, they found that a truck and a bakkie had collided with each other.While assessing the occupants of both the truck and bakkie, it was found that only the bakkie driver had sustained serious injuries. The man was stabilised on scene and thereafter transported to a nearby hospital under the constant care of an Advanced Life Support paramedic.The truck driver was not injured.Police are investigating the cause of the accident.